Let's consider an array `[a,b,c]`
So here total three senarios are possible
**Case 1:  a & ( b | c )**
so there will also be the snario for value a & ( c | b ), which cancel each other so their xor will be zero.
**Case 2 : a & ( b | b )**
This is an extended version of case 1, there will be only one pair for a & ( b | b ), but  there will also be the snario for value b & ( a | a ), which will cancel each other so their xor will be zero again.
**Case 3: a & ( a | a )**
 this is equal to `a`  and it is the only senario left in last , so their xor will be evluated as xor of all element.

