Why just xor of all the element in the array works? 


If we think about the triplet in the array at index i, j and k where i <= j <= k, there can be set of triplet.
(a, a, a)
(a, a, b)
(b, a, a)
(a, b, a)
(a, b, c)

If we pick triplet form the last (a, b, c) this can be cancel by the triplet (b, a, c) int the overall result because ((a | b) & c) = ((b | a) & c) and xor or 2 equal value will be 0.
In the same way 
(a | a) & b = (b | b) & a.
(b | a) & a = (a | b) & a.

we just have to consider the first case in the result which is the ((a | a) & a) = a.

