# Intuition
Since `x | y == y | x` all `nums[i] | nums[j]` for `i != j` will produce paris that cancel each other out, e.g. `(nums[i] | nums[j]) ^ (nums[j] | nums[i]) == 0` and each such pair will be tied to ` & nums[k]`, they will also cancel each other out. So the only ones that are going to be preserved are those that have `i == j`. So, in the end, we just need to xor all `nums`.

