# Intuition
Just XOR all the numbers to get your final answer. To understand the approach read below.

# Approach
There are three cases in this ques -
**1.** All the three numbers are same - 

in this case- (a|a)&a = a

**2.** Two of the numbers are same-

(a|b) & a = a , (a|b)&b = b , (a|a)&b= a&b, (b|b)&a = a&b, (b|a)&a = a, (b|a)&b = b

If you xor all the numbers above you will get-
(a^a) ^ (b^b) ^ (a&b ^ a&b) = 0

**3.** Similarly if all the three numbers are different then-
((a|b)&c) ^ ((b|a)&c) ^ ((a|c)&b) ^ ((c|a)&b) ^ ((b|c)&a) ^ ((c|b)&a) = 0

*So the final answer will be the xor of all the numbers present in the array.*


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(1)

